
This directory is intended for project specific (private) libraries.
PlatformIO will compile them to static libraries and link into the executable file.

The source code of each library should be placed in a separate directory
("lib/your_library_name/[Code]").

For example, see the structure of the following example libraries `Foo` and `Bar`:

|--lib
|  |
|  |--Bar
|  |  |--docs
# Project `lib` directory

This directory is intended for project-specific libraries used by this firmware.
PlatformIO will compile each library found under `lib/` into a static library and link it into the final executable.

Each library should live in its own subdirectory, e.g. `lib/Foo/` and `lib/Bar/`.

Example layout:

```
lib/
  ├─ Foo/
  │   ├─ src/
  │   │   └─ Foo.h
  │   │   └─ Foo.cpp
  │   └─ library.json  # optional
  └─ Bar/
      ├─ src/
      │   └─ Bar.h
      │   └─ Bar.cpp
      └─ docs/

src/
  └─ main.cpp
platformio.ini
```

Example usage in `src/main.cpp`:

```cpp
#include <Foo.h>
#include <Bar.h>

int main() {
  // ...
}
```

PlatformIO's Library Dependency Finder (LDF) automatically discovers and links libraries referenced by your source files. See:

- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html
